{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7231: hasOwnProperty('anyprop') gives false on build only",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:23.171401+00:00",
  "text": "hasOwnProperty('anyprop') gives false on build only\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.2.45\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://kasheftin.github.io/vue3-has-own-property-undefined/\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nJust open the page\r\nIt shows `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(this, 'prop1') = false`\n\n### What is expected?\n\nIt should show `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(this, 'prop1') = true`\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nHere's the source code: https://github.com/Kasheftin/vue3-has-own-property-undefined/blob/master/src/PropTest1.vue\r\nThis part causes the error:\r\n````javascript\r\nexport default {\r\n  ...\r\n  props: {\r\n    prop1: {\r\n      type: Number,\r\n      default: 0\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  computed: {\r\n    prop1Exists() {\r\n      return Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(this, 'prop1')\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n````\r\nThis code works just fine during the development. Since there's `prop1` prop, `this.prop1` is defined, and `Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty(this, 'prop1')` gives true. \r\n\r\nBut for some reason the build gives the different result. You can check it on https://kasheftin.github.io/vue3-has-own-property-undefined/. And this is very concerning, because it works on dev, and does not work on prod, and you find that it does not work only on production deployment.\r\n\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\nSystem:\r\n    OS: Linux 5.15 Ubuntu 20.04.5 LTS (Focal Fossa)\r\n    CPU: (12) x64 Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-8700 CPU @ 3.20GHz\r\n    Memory: 14.76 GB / 31.32 GB\r\n    Container: Yes\r\n    Shell: 5.0.17 - /bin/bash\r\n  Binaries:\r\n    Node: 16.14.2 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v16.14.2/bin/node\r\n    Yarn: 1.22.5 - ~/.yarn/bin/yarn\r\n    npm: 8.5.5 - ~/.nvm/versions/node/v16.14.2/bin/npm\r\n  Browsers:\r\n    Chrome: 105.0.5195.125\r\n    Firefox: 107.0\r\n  npmPackages:\r\n    vue: ^3.2.45 => 3.2.45\n```\n\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nIt would be nice to know the way to check if a propery exists that works on dev and on build. I'm interested in options-api way.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: reactivity",
    "🔩 p2-edge-case"
  ],
